-
-<p><a name="st_82"></a>
-<a name="07030520000016"></a><b><a name="70305-0006.htm_spnew4"></a><a name="07030520000399"></a>Lord Goodhart:</b> My Lords on the question of the publication of the report, I have been asked to chair a meeting on 14 March at Chatham House at which the noble Lord, Lord Carlile, will discuss his report. Does this mean that we will get the report before then?</p>
-
-<p><a name="st_83"></a>
-<a name="07030520000017"></a><b><a name="70305-0006.htm_spnew5"></a><a name="07030520000400"></a>Baroness Scotland of Asthal:</b> My Lords I have no idea. All I can tell your Lordships is that we have the report. It is being actively considered and consulted on now. I know that those who participate in Chatham House discussions are all absolutely trustworthy and would never breach the confidence which has been placed in them. So of course I can say nothing about that.</p>
