+<p><a name="st_107"></a>
+<a name="07030520000089"></a><b><a name="70305-0008.htm_spnew5"></a><a name="07030520000424"></a>Lord Howarth of Newport:</b> My Lords, my noble friend the Minister mentioned that today is the start of the debate, but does he accept that Mr Freud&#146;s recommendations that there should be more extensive use of private enterprise and voluntary sector welfare providers bear a close resemblance to the Wisconsin model, with which the Government were familiar nearly 10 years ago, and which then, as now, has significant merits in comparison to our traditional state bureaucratic model? Will he, however, take this opportunity to confirm that the Government have no intention whatever of emulating the excessively harsh, indeed cruel, withdrawal of benefits under the American system?</p>
 
