+<p><a name="07030544000070"></a>I notice the noble Lord, Lord Tomlinson, nodding in agreement with that proposition. If we can get to that position as a routine matter of regular, repeated behaviour, then great strides will be made. Although that would virtuously go beyond what national budget Ministers are prepared to do normally in their own national context in most member states, it would help to inspire confidence in a system where putting together 27 different national accounting and verification procedures is a nightmare at any time. But it must be achieved.</p>
