+<a name="07030544000036"></a><b><a name="70305-0014.htm_spnew5"></a><a name="07030544000091"></a>Lord Davies of Oldham:</b> My Lords, that was the whole point. There is investment in the Games, and the issue being debated was how we will get value in terms of the legacy, which I did not think that the noble Lord addressed. But that is last week&#146;s debate and this is this week&#146;s. I am very grateful for the opportunity to respond to this important debate. As my honourable friend the Economic Secretary to the Treasury made clear at the time, the Government very much congratulate the committee on the cogency of its analysis and particularly the chairmanship of my noble friend Lord Radice in producing this thorough, timely and persuasive work.</p>
 
